# Changelog Maintenance

When pushing changes or opening a PR, update `frontend/pages/ChangelogPage.tsx` if the work changes user-facing behavior, product copy, visible bug fixes, auth/security behavior, or database schema changes that users/admins need to know about.

- Add the newest entry at the top of `CHANGELOG`.
- Use a dated, versioned entry with high-level bullet points.
- Group related commits into one entry; do not dump raw commit messages.
- Do not add public changelog entries for internal-only work: CI, tests, package managers, npm/pnpm scripts, Dockerfile-only changes, docs-only changes, folder moves, formatting, or refactors with no observable product impact.
